added.title: TV Knight 8
added.description: Commissioner Gordon has to work, so Batman joins him at the GCPD for fun and crimefighting.

added.title: Winning a Golf Tournament Is the Solution to All of Life's Money Problems
added.description: After the T-Car is towed due to outstanding parking tickets, Robin has Cyborg enter a golf tournament for the cash prize.

added.title: Always Be Crimefighting
added.description: Looking to motivate them, Robin tells the Titans to solve some crimes or they're fired.

added.title: Easter Annihilation
added.description: When Cyborg's egg hunt tech stops working, the Titans go to their satellite to find out what happened.

added.title: The Brain of the Family
added.description: The Brain's home life is disrupted when his slacker brother Brian comes to visit. Now The Brain and Mallah have to deal with Brian's messes and keep him from ruining their big secret scheme.

added.title: Arthur
added.description: Robin threatens to fire Dr. Light unless he starts coming up with more inventive schemes.

added.title: Toilet Water
added.description: When the Titans dog-sit for Superman, Robin tries to keep the others from spoiling Krypto.

added.title: Plot Holes
added.description: After learning about movie plot holes, the Titans have some fun but end up throwing their world into chaos.

added.title: Utility Belt
added.description: Worried that he's only special because of his utility belt, Robin donates it to a thrift store.

added.title: Crab Shenanigans
added.description: Beast Boy, Negative Girl, and Robotman start hanging out with some punk crabs but soon discover the crabs are up to no good.

added.title: Brobots
added.description: Cyborg comes to visit Beast Boy, but once Cyborg realizes how much he and Robotman have in common, they become inseparable.

added.title: I'm the Sauce
added.description: Stuck inside because of bad weather, the Titans play rainy day games after Robin convinces them that indoor activities will cheer up the clouds and make the rain stop.

added.title: Pie Bros
added.description: Beast Boy has to get a job at a pie shop to earn enough money to buy Cyborg a birthday gift, only his job interferes with being able to attend the actual party.

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: The Brain
added.description: Anais has been facepalming every time her family does something stupid, which has led to a serious medical condition. In fact, if she facepalms just one more time she could do her brain irreparable damage, so the Wattersons have to get through the week without doing anything idiotic.

added.title: The Founder
added.description: When Nicole decides to pay the cable bill in person at Chanax, she leaves specific instructions for Richard to stay in the car. However he's far too tempted by the vending machine in the foyer to follow her advice. Chanax believes Richard is their mysterious founder and follow his every whim, leading to their inevitable demise.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Mothers
added.description: It's Mother's Day and kids put their moms through a series of tests to determine who has the World's Greatest Mom.  It's Mother's Day, and Gumball and Darwin discover that Tobias and Banana Joe have both made a card for "The Best Mom in the World". Clearly Nicole Watterson is the Best Mom, but Tobias and BJ just won't admit it... So they organise a mom-off at the mall between Nicole, Banana Barbara and Jackie Wilson. Needless to say it gets pretty intense.

added.title: The Procrastinators
added.description: Gumball and Darwin go to extraordinary lengths to avoid taking out the trash. Gumball and Darwin are offended when Mom calls them "procrastinators", once she's told them what it means. They promise to take the trash out by the time she gets home. As the clock slowly counts down, they discover that they will go to extraordinary lengths, no matter how inane, to avoid the task in hand.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Fridge
added.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: The Banana
added.description: Darwin lends his pen to Banana Joe but, when it comes back chewed, Gumball's thoughts turn to revenge.

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Carrie takes Gumball, Darwin and Anais to a real haunted house party on Halloween!

added.title: The Treasure
added.description: Anais uncovers a secret that she's convinced will lead her to the Watterson's hidden family treasure.

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: Rise and Shine
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part I: Craig goes on a sleepover adventure to Kelsey's house.

added.title: Sleep Talk JP
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part II: Another side of JP is revealed.

added.title: Toman's House
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part III: Craig steps inside Chateau de Toman aka the Castle of Wrassle aka Toman's House!

added.title: Whose Dimension Is It Anyway?
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part IV: Wren enlists Craig in a trans dimensional dream experiment.

added.title: Dude Where's My Bobby?
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part V: A night of candy brings out Craig and Bobby's inner bad boys.

added.title: The Slumber Party
added.description: The Sleepover Chronicles Part VI: Craig and friends compete in a series of cutthroat games to win Eliza's mystery prize.

added.title: The Elders of the Creek
added.description: The trio must reunite the Elders to save the Creek from an unexpected foe.

added.title: JP's Bucket list
added.description: The trio tries out some of JP's wildest ideas.

added.title: The Little Warrior
added.description: Searching for inspiration, Kelsey reads the tale of the Little Warrior.

added.title: See You Tomorrow at the Creek
added.description: The series finale of Craig of the Creek.

added.title: Fort Williams
added.description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
added.description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
added.description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.

added.title: West in Pieces
added.description: It's the old west and Mojo the Kid has robbed the first bank ever and forced the sheriff out of town and it is up to the Steamypuff Girls to save the day at a high-noon showdown.

added.title: Aspirations
added.description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

added.title: That's Not My Baby/Simian Says
added.description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. Can these three superheroes manage to take care of one little baby?/Simian Says: When the Narrator is mysteriously bound and gagged, Mojo Jojo takes over his job, ordering the girls to steal for him all around Townsville.

added.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
added.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

added.title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
added.description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: Summer Bummer
added.description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

added.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
added.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
added.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

added.title: The Kindergarten Kid
added.description: Steven and the Gems deal with a monster problem.

added.title: Know Your Fusion
added.description: Steven and the Gems delve deep into what makes a fusion so special.

added.title: Buddy's Book
added.description: Steven and Connie take a trip to the library and discover a long forgotten book.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Future Boy Zoltron
added.description: Steven fills in for a fortune teller at Funland.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Onion Gang
added.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

added.title: Gem Harvest
added.description: Steven's autumn visit to the barn brings a new stranger into his life.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.title: Steven's Dream
added.description: A strange dream prompts Steven to search for answers.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Lion 3: Straight to Video
added.description: Lion won't stop laying on Steven's face while he sleeps.

added.title: Rose's Scabbard
added.description: Steven joins Pearl on a special mission to a place that belonged to Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Mama Said
added.description: When King of Ooo sends Finn and Jake on a mission to catch flying mushrooms, they find their loyalty tested.

added.title: Wake Up
added.description: In order to find Finn's father, Finn and Jame must commit a cosmic crime unless the Lich beats them to it.

added.title: Escape from the Citadel
added.description: Finn and Jake follow the Lich of the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

added.title: James II
added.description: Finn and Jake discover Clone James has been faking his own death to collect medals. But there are 25 Jameses running amok!

added.title: The Tower
added.description: Finn doesn't like any of the new arms the princesses give him so he builds a tower into space to find his dad and get his old arm back.

added.title: Breezy
added.description: With a friendly bee named Breezy as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

added.title: Food Chain
added.description: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the food chain by becoming the food chain!

added.title: Sad Face
added.description: Once a month, while Jake's asleep, his tail stretches out of the treehouse to go work as a clown in a traveling bug circus.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: The Prince Who Wanted Everything
added.description: The beautiful and sensitive Lumpy Space Prince flees his cruel parents to start a new life.

added.title: Something Big
added.description: Princess Bubblegum must rally her forces when the Candy Kingdom is rocked by a massive assault.

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: A Bunch of Baby Ducks
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby come across a family of ducks living in a fountain at the park and take quite a shine to them.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Doctor Visit
added.description: Uncle Grandpa hates going to the doctor but he's overdue for an important vaccination.

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Sheep Deprivation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't fall asleep.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Surprise Party
added.description: Mr. Gus and Belly Bag are throwing a surprise party for Pizza Steve, as long as  Uncle Grandpa doesn't spoil their surprise.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: Aunt Grandma's back is causing more trouble for Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Belly Bros
added.description: When a kid is bummed that his favorite shirt won't fit over his big belly, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to show him that t-shirts come and go, but having a big belly is always cool.

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: Space Emperor
added.description: When UG mistakes a kid in a costume for an evil space emperor, he sends him to another dimension where he becomes an actual evil space emperor and UG must figure out some way to bring him home.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Moustache Cream
added.description: When UG and the gang are in a rush to purchase some emergency moustache cream, they face a formidable foe: Mart Mart.

added.title: Drawing Time
